@d97 1
a165 36
\begin{example}
Nonem is at the head of a party walking along a Black Mage's
well-guarded stone corridor.  He is checking the floor for magical
traps (central hex) every 5' and the space in front of him for wards
as they go.  Nonem's standard view is 60' ahead for checking wards (he
could have chosen 100', or any other number up to the limit of his
sight).  The scenario is something like this:

Staircase 1 is 20 steps, and wooden, Staircase 2 is 20 steps and
wooden, with a magical trap on step 11.  The party is travelling left
to right. Nonem's standard question is ``What is the Black Mage
Special Knowledge Spell in this ward/trap''.  The GM's answers
(assuming all are successful) might run like this:
\begin{flushleft}
Space: ``No aura for 60 ft'';
Floor: ``No aura 100 ft'';
Space: "Magical aura 20 ft away covering whole corridor, No answer''
(it is warded with a damnum minatum, a general knowledge spell);
Space: ``No aura next 60 ft'';
Floor: ``No aura next 40 ft'';
Floor: ``Magical aura on central hex of corridor, Hellfire'';
Space: ``No aura next 60', that is to top of stairs'';
Floor: ``next 20 ft to bottom of stair no aura'';
``First 10 steps formerly living'' (magical in any way?) ``no'',
``11th step is formerly living'' (magical in any way?) ``no";
``last 9 steps formerly living'' (magical in any way?) ``no'';
Space: ``no aura next 30', ie to top of stairs'';
``next 10' of corridor no aura'';
``first 10 steps formerly living'' (magical in any way?) ``no'';
``11 th step is formerly living'' (magical in any way?) ``yes'';
``remaining 9 steps formerly living" (magical in any way?) ``no'';
Space: ``No aura next 60 ft'';
Floor: ``next 100 ft no aura''.
\end{flushleft}
\end{example}

