The Base chance of the Detect Aura Talent is equal to the Adept's
modified Perception (twice modified Perception in the case of Namers),
modified by adding the following:

\begin{tabularx}{\linewidth}{Xr}
For every foot (after first 5 feet) separating the adept from target & -1 \\
For each Rank the adept has with the Detect Aura Talent & +5 \\
\end{tabularx}

d78 3
a80 1
To see an aura requires line of sight to the object being DAed.
d83 2
a84 2
Illusions do not provide an accompanying aura.  Thus the aura of an
illusion will always be magical.
