d126 10
a135 10
an answer of "no aura" would be given.  Similarly, if the attempt
succeeds, the aura may not be detected again to ask another question,
until next season.  The single attempt rule also applies to multi-hex
objects.  Only one DA may be performed per item -- one cannot DA a
wooden floor three times just because it covers 3 hexes.  Attempts to
do so will get the response (even before rolling the dice) -- ``you
see an aura, formerly living, and the answer is oak'', that is the
same aura they had previously read, which is free for the looking as
per rule 4, until a change of season.  After the change of season a
new attempt to detect the aura would have to be made.
