Stair 1 is 20 steps, and wooden, Stair 2 is 20 steps and wooden, with a
magical trap on step 11.  The party is travelling left to
right. Nonem's standard question is ``What is the Black Mage Special
Knowledge Spell in this ward/trap''.  The GM's answers (assuming all
are successful) might run like this:
d198 1
a201 13
For example an elf might have a visual-tactile illusion on his person
to make him look like a human.  A DA would reveal an aura of
``long-lived sentient being'', and Generic True Name would show as
elf.  Similarly a visual illusion of a pot-plant would have a magical
aura not formerly living), and a question like age might get "15
minutes".  There has been known to be an ``illusory aura'' spell.  In
this case one could add an aura to an illusion, or change the aura of
an object without changing anything else, for example changing the
aura on a cursed gem from magical to no aura.  This illusory aura can
be disbelieved in, at the usual difficulty factor based on the rank of
the spell.

